spanGrp.span: nam longbini ka nap pune punen soo
I want to tell a story.
mi wantem se mi talem wan stori
punen kiye usili yaapuo soo son san vanmoro
This story is about a man and his wife.
stori ya i abaot wan man wetem woman blong hem
san vanmoro mwi lingi saloo timaleh woróló
woman blong hem i bonem tu pikinini blong tufala
timaleh koloo ye koloo kevene kolom e man
The two children, both were male.
tufala pikinini ya tufala everiwan i man
timaleh koloo ye kolom du mane saloo tati mane saloo naana
The two children stayed with their daddy and their mother.
tufala pikinini ya tufala i stap wetem papa blong tufala wetem mama blong tufala
sori, saloo taata mane saloo naana
sorry, with their father and their mother.
sori, papa blong hem wetem mama blong hem
kolom du van van timaleh koloo ye kolom mee kolom bubo
The two lived on, the two children became big.
tufala i stap gogo tufala pikinini ya tufala i kam bigwan
tufala i askem tati blong tufala
komom longbini kop gone vihyee be woróló be somoo
we two want that you make two bow-and-arrows for us,
mitufala i wantem yu wokem tufala bonaro blong mitufala
byen ka komop pwet komop pyen ne
so that we can be shooting with them.
from bae mitufala i stap sut long hem
ngale saloo taata mwe kie ka, mu wuo gon
afta, tati blong tufala i talem se, i gud nomo
you wait, I will make them.
yutufala i wet, bae mi mekem
ngale mo gone saloo vihyee woróló
Then he made their two bow-and-arrows,
afta i wokem bonaro blong tufala
mwe sengane sen mane tamo, sen mane tato
he gave one to the firstborn, one to the secondborn,
i givim wan long fesbon, wan long lasbon
ngale kolom idi, leng soo kolom idi kolom du kolom pyen,
and they took them. One time, the two took them, they were shooting.
afta tufala i tekem, wan taem tufala i tekem tufala i stap sut
They shot at things, they shot at ants,
tufala i sutum, tufala i sutum anis
kolom du kolom pyen van lon duut, seesaa van lon duut, kolom vini basee
they were shooting into the bush, far away in the bush, they shot at birds.
tufala i stap tufala i sut go long bus, lowe i go long bus, tufala i sutum pijin
kolom pyen pyen van kolom vini basee soo lam kie me e bot piipili
They went on shooting, and they shot a bird, they call it "Red Head" (bot piipili).
tufala i sut sut gogo tufala i sutum wan pijin, oli kolem red hed
ngale tato en mwe seesaa ne
Then the secondborn took it and swayed it back and forth (while walking).
kolom vaaa vaaa vaaa lon too soo
Then they went on, and went into a garden.
afta tufala i go go go long wan garen
kolom lehe too kiye mu wuo
They saw that the garden was good.
tufala i luk garen ya i gud
kolom du kolom pyangbisi too kiye van kolom lehe vih soo
They kept checking out the garden, they saw a banana tree.
tufala i stap wajem garen ya gogo, tufala i luk wan banana
This banana tree had ripe fruits.
The bananas were ripe like that.
tamo en mwe kie ka bo pólo
The firstborn said that he would climb up,
fesbon i talem se bae i klaem
tato en mon mwe kie ka ngye mon bo pólo
the secondborn too said he too would climb up.
lasbon tu i talem se em tu bae i klaem
kolom du van kolom tubyek ne momiye van, tamo en mo winim mo pólo [tamo en san mwi yah nga mo pólo]
The two fought about this, and the first one won and climbed up.
tufala i go tufala i traem olsem gogo, fesbon i winim i klaem
mo pólo vih, vaa vaa, mo pwet lan liivih
He climbed up and was on top of the banana tree.
i klaem banana, gogo, i stap antap long banana tri
mwi idi vih myen, mu du ma ane, mwe lotmiyene taselan ke pwet lantan
He took a ripe banana and was eating it, he forgot about his brother who was on the ground.
i karem raep banana, i stap kakae, i fogetem brata blong hem we i stap daon
taselan ke mwe pwet lantan mwe kye, mwe kie, ey
His brother, who stayed down, called, Hey,
brata blong hem we i stap daon i singaot long hem, se Hey
sok biibilen, kop seene vih desoo mee nap ane
my brother, throw some banana to me so that I can eat it!
brata blong mi, yu sakem wan banana i kam mi kakae
tamo tere gone nomane ke ngye mwe kie
But the firstborn, he did not do as he said.
be fesbon hem i no mekem olsem we hem i talem
mwi idi belere, mwe kyep lon belere, mwe seene mee lantan
Instead, he took a banana peel, he shat into the banana peel and throw it down.
i tekem skin blong hem, i sisit long skin blong hem, i sakem i kam daon
tato mwe lehe momiye, mo longane mwe sanga
The younger one saw that, and felt bad.
lasbon i luk olsem, i harem i nogud
mo vatahe van, Ey, kop sengane vih myen desoo mee nap ane!
He repeated, Hey, throw some ripe banana to me so that I can eat it!
i talem bakagen i go, Ey, yu sakem wan raep banana i kam mi kakae
ngale ngye ma ane monok, mwe kyep lon belere mwe seene mee lantan
After the older brother finished eating, he shat into a banana peel and threw it down,
afta hem i kakae finis, i sisit long skin blong hem, i sakem i kam daon
mo gone tato en mo longane ma sanga
which made the younger one feel bad.
i mekem lasbon i harem i nogud
mwe elehe ngye mo kuo morone taselan ke tamo me mee tyenem
He turned around and ran away from his older brother and came home.
i tanem hem i ron we long fesbon brata blong hem i kam long haos
me mee me mee mwe tangale ot tyenem, mu yongyong
He reached his home place, and he washed himself.
i kam i kam i kasem haos, i swim
monok, mwi idi volon bot piipili ke kolom vini ye
Then he took a feather of the redhead bird that he had shot,
finis, i tekem feta blong red hed we tufala i sutum ya
and stuck it into his hair.
i pusum long hea blong hem
monok, mwe kie mane san tuutu vaven
This done, he said to his grandmother,
afta, i talem long abu woman blong hem
mwe kie, tuutu, ngyo nap van ngiye
i talem, abu woman, mi mi go nao
san tuutu mwe kie, kop van okobe?, mwe kie, nap van ngiye
His grandmother said, where will you go? He said, I will go now.
abu blong hem i talem, yu go wea?, hem i talem, mi go nao
mu du dumuo, me van lereh san tuutu mu du duto ne
He went ahead, he went to the beach, his grandmother was follwoing him.
i go festaim, i go long solwota, abu blong hem i folem hem
mwe van, van van van, tangale ot lan womela
He went on and reached the beach.
i go go go go, kasem ples long sanbij
san tuutu mwe lehe ke mu duusili womela me van saa lon teh
His grandmother saw that he went along the beach all the way to the the sea.
abu blong hem i luk we i folem sanbij i go olwe long solwota
She said, where will you go?
mu wisi, mwe kie, nap van ngiye
She asked, he said, I will go now.
i askem, i talem, mi go nao
me van bili ke me metu lon teh, mwe kolyet
He went, when he stood in the seawater, he sang.
i go taem i stanap long solwota, i singsing
san tuutu mwe tahpwet lan womela
His grandmother sat down on the beach.
abu blong hem i isdaen i stap long sanbij
mo longane ke timaleh man ku muru ye mo kolyet
She heard that the small boy was sang.
i harem smol boe ya i singsing
an vaven kekei oo, kom mee, dop van gere, kom mee dop van gere
My girl oo, you came, we two will go into the sea, you came, we two will go into the sea.
smol gel oo, yu kam, yumitu go long solwota
mo kolyet, a mo loko teh monok, lan yen okele monok
He sang, and he walked towards the sea, up to his legs here.
i singsing, i wokbaot, solwota i finis long leg blong hem ples ya
san tuutu mwe kie ka, kop mee, kop kuoli mee dop van tyenem
His grandmother said, you come, You come back to me, we two will go home!
abu blong hem i talem se, yu kam, yu kambak yumitu go long haos
But he went on, and sang again.
hem i go, i singsing bakagen
bot piipili, bot piipili, dop van behe, kom mee, dop van gere
Redhead, Redhead, where will we go? You came, we will go into the sea.
redhed, redhed, bae yumi go wea, yu kam, bae yumi go long solwota.
an vaven kekei oo, kom mee dop van gere, kom mee dop van gere
My small woman, oh, you came, we two will go into the sea, you came, we two will go into the sea.
smol gel blong mi, oh, yu kam, bae yumi go long solwota, yu kam, bae yumi go long solwota
mo loko van, teh monok okele monok, monok lan weyiyeén
He went on, and the sea went up to here, up to his chest.
i wokbaot i go, solwota i kasem ples ya finis long jes blong hem
mu byene velan, mwe kie, kop mee, mee dop kuoli van tyenem, mabyok kulu kom mee nam longane ma sanga byen ngyak
She threw her arms up, she said, You come, we two will go back home, my small grandchild, I feel very bad for you!
i sakem han blong hem, i tale, yu kam, yumitu gobak long haos, smol abu blong mi, mi harem nogud from yu
san tuutu mo longane mwe sanga, mwe kie
His grandmather felt very bad, she said,
abu blong hem i harem nogud, i singaot
The sea now reached under his neck,
solwota i finis long nek blong hem
san tuutu mwe kye, ngye tere teemee ne san tuutu
His grandmother called, but he did not see his grandmother.
abu blong hem i singaot, em i no lukluk i kam long abu blong hem
mo loko me van, mwe kolyet teteh, mo kolyet
He went on, he sang again.
i wokbaot i go, i singsing bakagen
bot piipili, bot piipili, dop van behe, kom mee, dop van gere, kom mee dop van gere, an vaven kekei oo, kom mee dop van gere
Redhed, Redhed, where will we go? You came, we will go into the sea, you came, we will go into the sea. My girl, oh, you came, we will go into the sea.
redhed, redhet, bae yumitu go wea, yu kam, bae yumitu go long solwota, yu kam, bae yumitu go long solwota, smol woman blong mi, oh, yu kam, bae yumitu go long solwota
when he sang the whole song,
taem i singsing flatem singsing ya
the sea was covering his head.
solwota i kaveremap hed blong hem
vot soo mwe pwese pwet lan baren
A rock is standing at the place of his head,
wan ston i stanap long hed blong hem
abu blong hem tu i krae
mwe pepeleh lan womela, yaa soo mwe en mwi yah
She was shaking on the beach, the sun was burning very strong.
i saksakem leg long sanbij, san i saen strong
yaa kiye ma ane san tuutu vaven gon van
san ya wi kakae abu woman blong hem
san tuutu vaven mwe deng gon van yaa kiye mwe enbini
His grandmother was crying, the sun was burning her to death.
abu woman blong hem i krae gogo san ya i bonem em i ded
san tuutu vaven me metpwet lan womela
His grandmother was dead at the beach.
abu woman blong hem i ded i stap long sanbij
taselan ke tamo me mee mu wisi, taselok ke tato?
His elder brother came and asked, where is my younger brother?
fesbon brata blong hem i kam i askem, lasbon brata blong mi?
lam kie san naana son san taata kolom kie mo longane mwe sanga kom sengane wili vih myen mane
They said, your mother and your father, they feel very bad that you threw the banana skin to him.
oli talem mama blong yu wetem tati blong yu tufala i talem se i harem i nogud from yu givim skin blong raep banana long hem
lonla kele mo loko van teh mwe pándingi
Now he went away, and the sea has drowned him.
naoya i wokbaot i go, solwota i draonem hem
mwe kihne kop lehe vot korok
They pointed out, You sea that rock there?
i pointem, yu luk ston ya lowe
brata blong yu em i stap ples ya
a bwé ke nam kolyet ne mwe pwet
But the song that I sang of him exists till now.
be singsing we mi sing long hem i stap ya
bot piipili bot piipili me e basee ke mi vini lon duut
The redhead is the bird that he shot in the bush.
redhed redhed emi pijin we i sutum long bus
lam kye san ih me e bot piipili, mwe pwese ne mwe pwet lan volon
They call it "Redhead", he stuck its feather into his hair.
oli singaoutem nem blong hem emi redhed, i putum i stap long hea blong hem
mo loko mane van, be mo kolyet ne bot piipili
He walked with it, and he sang about the Redhead.
i wokbaot wetem i go, be i stap singsing long redhed
kiye gon me e sadyee punpunen ke doma, sipa ten
This is our story of today, thank you very much.
emya nomo i story blong yumi blong tede, tankyu tumas
